In other corners of the internet, Web 1.0 aesthetics have never disappeared.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://luckysoap.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 My own website}}, including this page, which uses fixed-width table cells, is based on a template I created in HomeSite in 1997.\
\
Web 1.0 aesthetics persist in source code and stated objectives of the massive\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.ubuweb.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 Ubu Web}}\'a0site, an "independent resource dedicated to all strains of the avant-garde, ethnopoetics, and outsider arts." On 16 December 2014, the founder of\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/ubuweb/status/545074372093165568"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 boasted on Twitter}}\'a0that "the whole damn site is still hand-coded in html 1.0 in bbedit, from templates made in 1996."\
\
I shall put off updating my website templates until out-of-date design is no longer cool.\
\
